The '''Draggulch Period''' was an era of galactic history that coincided with the [[New Sith Wars]], a [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy-spanning]] conflict that lasted from [[2000 BBY/Legends|2000 BBY]] to [[1000 BBY/Legends|1000 BBY]].

Historically and archaeologically, some cultures that flourished in that period of history had to display several technological artifacts that were forgotten by cultures of later ages, such as healing machines as effective as the much later [[bacta/Legends|bacta]], [[food rations]] that remained fresh for centuries thanks to a technology similar to [[stasis field/Legends|stasis field]], [[Tractor_beam_projector/Legends|Tractor beam projectors]] as small as hand-held wand, portable [[fusion generator/Legends|fusion reactors]] that could be carried in backpacks. In the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Era]] larger devices for the same functions were used, and the finding of such during the excavations of the [[Valley of the Jedi]] impressed the agents of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].<ref name="Dark Forces: Jedi Knight">''[[Dark Forces: Jedi Knight]]''</ref>

